oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Three views of Buford College
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Three views of Buford College, Church Street at 21st Avenue in Nashville. Shows "Burgess Hall"; "A Corner of Studio"; and "Pillars On North Front."
Buford College was a school for women that was originally founded by Mary Elizabeth Burgess Buford in Clarksville. The school moved to Nashville in 1901 and it closed in 1920.
